1
00:00:13,160 --> 00:00:13,720
Don't move.

2
00:00:14,760 --> 00:00:17,320
I am He Qi, the Daye Kingdom's greatest spy.

3
00:00:17,720 --> 00:00:18,520
He Qi.

4
00:00:19,080 --> 00:00:20,280
Do you know who these two are?

5
00:00:21,120 --> 00:00:22,080
That fat one...

6
00:00:22,440 --> 00:00:23,640
...is General Wei Long.

7
00:00:23,880 --> 00:00:24,600
The skinny one...

8
00:00:24,600 --> 00:00:25,520
...is their Strategist.

9
00:00:25,560 --> 00:00:26,360
Yuwen Liang.

10
00:00:26,640 --> 00:00:27,080
Boss.

11
00:00:27,080 --> 00:00:27,920
How do you know everything?

12
00:00:28,680 --> 00:00:30,480
I am the Daye Kingdom's greatest spy, after all.

13
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:33,400
Are you okay?

14
00:00:33,520 --> 00:00:34,280
I'm fine.

15
00:00:34,280 --> 00:00:35,160
Just a bit dizzy.

16
00:00:35,400 --> 00:00:36,040
Are you okay?

17
00:00:36,080 --> 00:00:36,920
I'm fine.

18
00:00:37,400 --> 00:00:38,040
With me here,

19
00:00:38,360 --> 00:00:39,720
I won't let them hurt you.

20
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:41,720
Still being lovey-dovey at a time like this?

21
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:43,040
Then let's do this.

22
00:00:43,360 --> 00:00:44,000
Boss!

23
00:00:45,520 --> 00:00:46,040
Stop fighting!

24
00:00:46,040 --> 00:00:46,880
We got the Jar!

25
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:47,720
Put the Jar down.

26
00:00:50,480 --> 00:00:51,280
Don't come any closer!

27
00:00:51,360 --> 00:00:52,480
Come closer and I'll smash the Jar!

28
00:00:52,840 --> 00:00:54,160
Smash it and I'll kill you.

29
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:55,600
Kill me and I'll smash it.

30
00:00:55,760 --> 00:00:56,440
Stop!

31
00:01:25,240 --> 00:01:26,160
Amazing.

32
00:01:26,840 --> 00:01:27,920
What do they do?

33
00:01:28,040 --> 00:01:28,960
Judging by their moves,

34
00:01:29,040 --> 00:01:29,880
they're no ordinary people.

35
00:01:30,360 --> 00:01:31,480
Opera singers.

36
00:01:31,680 --> 00:01:32,680
What play is this?

37
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:33,800
They even have to jump in the water.

38
00:01:33,960 --> 00:01:34,960
Must be "Havoc in the Dragon Palace".

39
00:01:35,680 --> 00:01:36,880
We have to watch this closely.

40
00:01:45,200 --> 00:01:47,520
They haven't come out for so long.

41
00:01:48,160 --> 00:01:49,280
Then let's save them.

42
00:01:59,800 --> 00:02:01,280
Where is this?

43
00:02:01,720 --> 00:02:02,320
A sword!

44
00:02:02,880 --> 00:02:03,600
General Wei.

45
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:04,680
Don't be rash.

46
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:08,480
You don't be rash first.

47
00:02:09,040 --> 00:02:10,280
You don't be rash either.

48
00:02:11,280 --> 00:02:12,600
Then I'll just be rash.

49
00:02:13,560 --> 00:02:15,120
Let's see who's really rash.

50
00:02:16,040 --> 00:02:18,120
You're all being too rash.

51
00:02:18,920 --> 00:02:20,280
Can't a person get some sleep?

52
00:02:24,080 --> 00:02:26,400
W-What is this situation?

53
00:02:38,320 --> 00:02:38,840
Where's the Jar?

54
00:02:40,200 --> 00:02:41,120
We didn't take the Jar.

55
00:02:41,760 --> 00:02:42,800
You took it and won't admit it.

56
00:02:43,040 --> 00:02:43,960
If we had taken the Jar,

57
00:02:43,960 --> 00:02:45,120
would we still be spinning in circles with you here?

58
00:02:45,120 --> 00:02:45,480
Exactly.

59
00:02:47,240 --> 00:02:47,840
Sister-in-law, are you okay?

60
00:02:48,320 --> 00:02:48,760
I'm fine.

61
00:02:48,760 --> 00:02:49,680
Just a bit dizzy from spinning.

62
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:50,880
Brother, Sister-in-law,

63
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:52,440
that team of yours,

64
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:53,920
sure has a lot of stories.

65
00:02:54,480 --> 00:02:55,600
My head is spinning too.

66
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:56,520
Can we stop spinning?

67
00:02:56,680 --> 00:02:57,040
This...

68
00:02:57,040 --> 00:02:57,840
They stop first.

69
00:02:58,280 --> 00:02:59,040
Why should we stop first?

70
00:02:59,040 --> 00:02:59,760
You got dizzy first.

71
00:02:59,760 --> 00:03:00,600
You stop first.

72
00:03:00,600 --> 00:03:01,320
I'm not dizzy.

73
00:03:01,320 --> 00:03:02,040
Aqin is dizzy.

74
00:03:02,600 --> 00:03:02,960
Stop!

75
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:13,240
Over here.

76
00:03:13,640 --> 00:03:14,160
Over here.

77
00:03:18,960 --> 00:03:19,640
Stop it!

78
00:03:19,680 --> 00:03:20,400
Don't move!

79
00:03:21,880 --> 00:03:23,120
You're finally awake.

80
00:03:23,440 --> 00:03:25,080
You slept for three days and three nights.

81
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:26,400
In the village...

82
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:27,800
...fighting is not allowed.

83
00:03:28,160 --> 00:03:29,160
No, who are you?

84
00:03:29,160 --> 00:03:30,160
I am a General of the Kingdom of Dawei...

85
00:03:30,160 --> 00:03:30,520
Wei...

86
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:34,720
Be good.

87
00:03:34,880 --> 00:03:35,520
Stop fussing.

88
00:03:35,880 --> 00:03:36,400
Thank you for your trouble.

89
00:03:36,680 --> 00:03:37,240
Stop it!

90
00:03:37,760 --> 00:03:39,840
I am the Strategist of the Kingdom of Dawei, Yuwen Liang.

91
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:42,080
Watch the steps. Watch the steps.

92
00:03:42,760 --> 00:03:43,880
I hope the three of you...

93
00:03:43,880 --> 00:03:45,600
...will help us catch these villains.

94
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:47,400
Let's sit over there and rest a bit.

95
00:03:47,960 --> 00:03:49,440
I will surely report this to the Lord...

96
00:03:49,440 --> 00:03:50,560
...and you will be heavily rewarded.

97
00:03:50,680 --> 00:03:51,400
Sit, sit, sit.

98
00:03:52,480 --> 00:03:54,480
As citizens of the Kingdom of Dawei...

99
00:03:54,560 --> 00:03:55,840
...this is your duty.

100
00:03:56,160 --> 00:03:57,000
The Kingdom of Dawei?

101
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:58,360
Never heard of it.

102
00:03:58,440 --> 00:04:00,160
Then you must be citizens of the Daye Kingdom.

103
00:04:00,560 --> 00:04:01,720
If you help our Daye Kingdom...

104
00:04:01,720 --> 00:04:02,240
Capture

105
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:02,560
and seize

106
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:02,880
the

107
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:03,400
villains

108
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:05,680
Our Daye Kingdom will treat you well.

109
00:04:07,520 --> 00:04:08,520
Daye?

110
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:09,880
Never heard of that either.

111
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:10,240
Wait.

112
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:12,840
Then who do you belong to?

113
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:14,600
What do you mean, "belong to"?

114
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:16,680
Our ancestors fled the chaos of the Qin Dynasty.

115
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:19,200
Leading their families to this isolated place...

116
00:04:19,400 --> 00:04:20,480
...they never left again.

117
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:22,520
Thus, we were cut off from the outside world.

118
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:23,800
Regardless of the Wei or Jin Dynasties...

119
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:24,840
...we know nothing of the Han.

120
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:25,800
That's right.

121
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:29,760
No need to mention this to outsiders.

122
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:30,720
Sir...

123
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:31,880
...could this be...

124
00:04:31,880 --> 00:04:33,320
...the legendary Shangri-La?

125
00:04:35,760 --> 00:04:36,560
Shangri-La?

126
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:37,360
You flatter us.

127
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:39,360
We just live far from conflict.

128
00:04:40,840 --> 00:04:42,280
I am Hu Lu...

129
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:43,920
...the Village Chief here.

130
00:04:44,880 --> 00:04:45,600
This is...

131
00:04:45,760 --> 00:04:46,880
...Security Chief Da Qiang.

132
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:48,920
And this is...

133
00:04:48,920 --> 00:04:49,960
...my daughter, Xiao Hua.

134
00:04:57,560 --> 00:04:58,240
Xiao Hua...

135
00:04:59,040 --> 00:04:59,920
...read everyone...

136
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:01,640
...our village rules.

137
00:05:01,640 --> 00:05:02,680
What bullshit village rules?

138
00:05:02,680 --> 00:05:03,240
I'm not listening!

139
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:04,000
We're done here.

140
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:04,680
We're leaving now.

141
00:05:05,960 --> 00:05:06,360
Don't go!

142
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:07,200
Where do you think you're going?

143
00:05:09,320 --> 00:05:11,000
You'll suffer if you don't listen to the rules!

144
00:05:11,120 --> 00:05:11,640
Come back!

145
00:05:14,880 --> 00:05:15,680
They won't listen.

146
00:05:15,960 --> 00:05:16,440
I'll listen.

147
00:05:17,840 --> 00:05:19,040
General, you may not know this...

148
00:05:19,240 --> 00:05:19,960
...but our ancestors...

149
00:05:19,960 --> 00:05:21,440
...to protect the village...

150
00:05:21,440 --> 00:05:22,360
...set up a Mist Barrier.

151
00:05:22,840 --> 00:05:24,080
Only our people have lived here...

152
00:05:24,080 --> 00:05:25,200
...for generations.

153
00:05:25,320 --> 00:05:27,280
Outsiders cannot enter or leave.

154
00:05:28,080 --> 00:05:28,960
As for you...

155
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:30,200
...arriving here by accident...

156
00:05:30,320 --> 00:05:32,080
...must be a stroke of fate.

157
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:34,240
It... it just means we're destined to meet.

158
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:39,760
Then tell me the village rules.

159
00:05:40,760 --> 00:05:41,240
Okay.

160
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:43,400
Village rule number one:

161
00:05:43,400 --> 00:05:44,360
No fighting.

162
00:05:46,120 --> 00:05:46,760
And then?

163
00:05:47,840 --> 00:05:48,400
That's it.

164
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:50,480
Just one rule.

165
00:06:05,760 --> 00:06:06,520
Darn it.

166
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:07,640
What do we do?

167
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:08,560
Yeah...

168
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:10,120
...what should we do?

169
00:06:10,920 --> 00:06:11,880
The Jar isn't fixed...

170
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:13,040
...and we lost it.

171
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:35,480
Look.

172
00:06:35,880 --> 00:06:37,080
A newly woven grass knot.

173
00:06:37,760 --> 00:06:38,480
Tell me.

174
00:06:38,760 --> 00:06:39,960
Who is the spy?

175
00:06:40,080 --> 00:06:41,440
Don't point at her.

176
00:06:41,640 --> 00:06:42,320
What's the matter?

177
00:06:42,320 --> 00:06:43,640
Everything requires evidence.

178
00:06:43,640 --> 00:06:44,520
Does this even need evidence?

179
00:06:44,520 --> 00:06:45,560
Let's go over it from the start.

180
00:06:46,520 --> 00:06:47,880
Who found the Grass marker last time?

181
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:49,000
It was me too.

182
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:53,080
So I'm the spy?

183
00:06:54,440 --> 00:06:55,640
How come I don't know that?

184
00:06:56,920 --> 00:06:57,560
Wei Long.

185
00:06:58,080 --> 00:06:59,520
I really wish you were a spy.

186
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:02,000
Then the Daye Kingdom would have fallen long ago.

187
00:07:04,040 --> 00:07:04,600
Miss.

188
00:07:04,840 --> 00:07:05,680
Don't keep squatting on the ground.

189
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:06,320
It's cold.

190
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:15,320
It smells so good.

191
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:16,880
That makes sense.

192
00:07:20,760 --> 00:07:21,520
So...

193
00:07:21,760 --> 00:07:23,400
General Wei has been suspecting me all along.

194
00:07:24,280 --> 00:07:25,280
In that case...

195
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:27,360
I should part ways with everyone.

196
00:07:27,880 --> 00:07:29,400
The village is safe anyway.

197
00:07:29,640 --> 00:07:30,520
Say no more.

198
00:07:31,440 --> 00:07:33,440
Your memory hasn't returned yet.

199
00:07:33,760 --> 00:07:35,560
I won't let you leave alone.

200
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:37,640
Miss, please rest assured.

201
00:07:37,960 --> 00:07:38,880
I, the Strategist...

202
00:07:39,120 --> 00:07:40,640
...will definitely keep you safe.

203
00:07:42,640 --> 00:07:43,840
Thank you, Mr. Yuwen.

204
00:07:43,840 --> 00:07:44,640
No need for formalities.

205
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:48,040
By the way.

206
00:07:48,640 --> 00:07:50,880
The Grass marker in General Wei's hand just now...

207
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:51,960
I think I recognize it.

208
00:07:52,320 --> 00:07:52,760
Recognize?

209
00:07:53,080 --> 00:07:54,320
Then... then what does it mean?

210
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:55,920
I don't know either.

211
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:58,440
It just looks familiar.

212
00:07:59,120 --> 00:08:00,280
Familiar?

213
00:08:02,360 --> 00:08:02,880
Quick, quick, quick.

214
00:08:02,880 --> 00:08:04,160
Sit down and rest a bit.

215
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:06,720
Careful, careful.

216
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:09,600
Thank you, Mr. Yuwen.

217
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:10,880
Do not rush.

218
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:11,880
When you remember...

219
00:08:11,880 --> 00:08:13,200
...it won't be too late to tell me.

220
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:16,600
I've troubled you, Mr. Yuwen.

221
00:08:16,760 --> 00:08:17,600
Not at all.

222
00:08:18,080 --> 00:08:18,880
General.
